Crédit Agricole S.A. provides various retail, corporate, and investment banking products and services worldwide. The company offers retail banking and financial services, including savings products, such as money market, bonds, and securities; lending products comprising mortgage loans and consumer finance;… MoreCrédit Agricole S.A. provides various retail, corporate, and investment banking products and services worldwide. The company offers retail banking and financial services, including savings products, such as money market, bonds, and securities; lending products comprising mortgage loans and consumer finance; life, property and casualty, and death and disability insurance; and payment services to individual customers, farmers, small businesses, medium-sized enterprises, corporates, and local authorities. It also provides specialized financial services, such as factoring and lease finance; asset management services, which include savings solutions for individuals and investment solutions for institutional clients; investor services, such as custody services, depositary/trustee services, fund administration, and issuer services; and creditor insurance services, as well as various private banking and wealth management services.

Procurement Process:

The company has a "Responsible Supplier Relations Charter" that it signed in 2010 in order to keep a balanced relationship with its suppliers. The charter is comprised of ten commitments related to responsible purchasing and lasting refashions as well as environmental impact issues, financial equity, and dependency risk.
IT Bytes

• Credit Agricole recently opened its new data center which is comprised of 2 sites, both located in Chartres, France (60 miles from Paris) and in which all data for Credit Agricole and its subsidiaries is stored. CA Immobilier… MoreIT Bytes

• Credit Agricole recently opened its new data center which is comprised of 2 sites, both located in Chartres, France (60 miles from Paris) and in which all data for Credit Agricole and its subsidiaries is stored. CA Immobilier strategically developed the sites to maximize energy efficiency as well as promote green IT.
• The company recently outsourced its decision support capabilities to Teradata who integrated business intelligence systems, supported a CRM program with Teradata active data warehouse, and migrated data using Teradata virtual storage.





